<dl id="n08053j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08053j">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08053j"> 53(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> broken = asthma</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><i>L&apos;&eacute;criture bris&eacute;e</i> est caract&eacute;ris&eacute;e par une interruption plus ou moins &eacute;tendue du trac&eacute; des lettres &hellip; (fig. 95). Ce signe est li&eacute; aux troubles de la respiration et de la circulation. <br><font color="green">[Broken writing is characterised by a more or less extended interruption of the strokes of the letters [&hellip;]</font> (fig. 95). This symptom has been linked to respiratory or circulatory problems.] <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 192</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
